
@startuml

' Define classes
class Cinema {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -location: String
  +getTheatres(): List<Theatre>
}

class Theatre {
  -id: int
  -cinema: Cinema
  -name: String
  -capacity: int
  +getShows(): List<Show>
}

class Movie {
  -id: int
  -title: String
  -duration: int
  +getTitle(): String
}

class MovieCopy {
  -id: int
  -movie: Movie
  -cinema: Cinema
  -location: String
  +getLocation(): String
}

class Show {
  -id: int
  -theatre: Theatre
  -movie: Movie
  -startTime: DateTime
  -endTime: DateTime
  -published: boolean
  +getAvailableSeats(): int
  +cancelShow(): void
}

class Reservation {
  -id: int
  -show: Show
  -customer: Customer
  -seatNumber: int
  -paymentStatus: PaymentStatus
  -reservedAt: DateTime
  +cancelReservation(): void
}

enum PaymentStatus {
  PENDING
  PAID
  REFUNDED
}

class Customer {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -email: String
  -creditCard: String
  +makeReservation(show: Show, seat: int): Reservation
  +cancelReservation(reservation: Reservation): void
  +acceptOffer(offer: Offer): void
}

class Offer {
  -id: int
  -reservation: Reservation
  -newShow: Show
  -createdAt: DateTime
  -expiresAt: DateTime
  +sendOffer(): void
  +isExpired(): boolean
}

class Ticket {
  -id: int
  -show: Show
  -seatNumber: int
  -customer: Customer
  -type: TicketType
}

enum TicketType {
  ONLINE_RESERVATION
  CASH_PURCHASE
}

class CashPurchase {
  -id: int
  -ticket: Ticket
  -purchaseTime: DateTime
}

' Define relationships
Cinema "1" --> "0..*" Theatre
Theatre "1" --> "0..*" Show
Movie "1" --> "0..*" MovieCopy
MovieCopy "1" --> "1" Cinema
Show "1" --> "0..*" Reservation
Reservation "1" --> "1" Customer
Customer "1" --> "0..*" Reservation
Customer "1" --> "0..*" Offer
Offer "1" --> "1" Reservation
Offer "1" --> "1" Show
Show "1" --> "0..*" Ticket
Ticket "1" --> "1" TicketType
Ticket "1" --> "0..1" CashPurchase

@enduml

---

### 📌 Notes:

- **Cinema** contains multiple **Theatres**, which in turn have multiple **Shows**.
- Each **Show** is associated with a specific **Movie** and a **Theatre**.
- A **Movie** can have multiple **MovieCopies**, each located in a **Cinema**.
- **Reservations** are made by **Customers** for **Shows** and are linked to a **PaymentStatus**.
- **Offers** are sent when a **Show** is cancelled and a new one is available; these are tied to **Reservations**.
- **Tickets** can be either from online reservations or purchased at the entrance (cash purchase).
- **CashPurchases** are anonymous and not refundable.

